thread.title: U.S. Government Bond Prices Jump on Dovish Fed, Trump’s Tariff Proposals

author: Daniel Kruger
title: U.S. Government Bond Prices Jump on Dovish Fed, Trump’s Tariff Proposals

organizations.name: u.s. government bond prices jump on dovish fed

text:
U.S. government bond prices rose as investors reassessed the economic landscape following dovish minutes from the Federal Reserve’s May meeting and new tariff proposals from President Donald Trump.
The yield on the benchmark 10-year Treasury note fell for a second consecutive session to 2.981% from 3.003% Wednesday, notching its biggest two-day decline since March 1. Yields fall as bond prices rise.
